<plot>Kuleshov's Cabinet uses four archival films to illustrate the transformation of the automobile as an iconic American image of freedom and innovation to a symbol of death and oppression. Using the principle of the Kuleshov Effect, it is a funeral march evoking notions of oil wars, car bombs, global erosion of freedoms and civil liberties and the paradoxical image of the car as a symbol of modernization.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?298738</url></doc>
